subsection.def:
Board
                    (存保委員會) means the Hong Kong Deposit
                Protection Board established by section 3;

depositor
                    (存款人) means a person entitled to repayment of
                a deposit, whether made by him or not;

director
                    (董事) includes any person who occupies the
                position of director, whatever the title of his office;

Fund
                    (存保基金) means the Deposit Protection Scheme
                Fund established by section 14;

paragraph.content:
reflects the Monetary Authority’s assessment of the Scheme member’s
                        overall financial condition and of the quality of the Scheme member’s
                        management;

subsection.def:
Scheme
                    (存保計劃) means the Deposit Protection Scheme
                established under section 11;

Tribunal
                    (審裁處) means the Deposit Protection Appeals
                Tribunal established by section 40;

paragraph.content:
in relation to the bank’s depositors, means the time when the bank
                        receives the notice of decision of the Board given under subsection
                        (6);

subparagraph.content:
incorporate his decision, the reasons for his decision, and the Scheme
                        member’s representations, if any, in his report to the Chief Executive in
                        Council;

subsection.def:
excluded transfer (不適用轉讓) means a transfer by way of a property transfer instrument within
                the meaning of section 2 of Schedule 4 to the Financial Institutions
                (Resolution) Ordinance (Cap. 628);

paragraph.content:
the protected deposits maintained with one or more of the transferors
                        in the arrangement are transferred, under the arrangement, to the resulting
                        Scheme member in the arrangement;

a person maintained protected deposits with 2 or more Scheme members
                    involved in the qualifying arrangement immediately before the material date
                            (affected person);

paragraph.continued:
regardless of the number or amount of deposits the person maintained with
                    the resulting Scheme member during the enhanced protection period;
                    or

subparagraph.content:
afford the Board, or a person appointed as an agent of the Board or
                        authorized by the Board under this Ordinance, access to those records;
                        and

paragraph.content:
to the disclosure of information in summary form that is so framed as to
                    prevent particulars relating to the business of any particular Scheme member
                    from being ascertained from it;

to the disclosure of information with a view to the institution of, or
                    otherwise for the purpose of, any criminal proceedings, whether under this
                    Ordinance or otherwise;

to the disclosure of information to the police or the Independent
                    Commission Against Corruption, at the request of the Secretary for Justice,
                    relevant to the proper investigation of any criminal complaint;

to the disclosure of information to an auditor, or a former auditor, of a
                    Scheme member or former Scheme member for the purpose of enabling or assisting
                    the Board to perform its functions under this Ordinance;

subsection.def:
adequate
                    (足夠), in relation to systems of control,
                includes operating effectively;

*commencement
                    date (生效日期) means the date of
                commencement of the Deposit Protection Scheme (Amendment) Ordinance 2016 (2 of 2016);

paragraph.content:
for determining the amount of build-up levy payable by a Scheme member
                    under section 3(5) of Schedule 4 for the year of 2016;
                    and

a structured deposit;
                    (Added L.N. 107 of
                            2006)

a structured deposit;
                    (Added L.N. 107 of
                            2006)

may, in or outside the place where it is incorporated, lawfully take
                        deposits from the general public (whether or not on current account), or is
                        authorized or recognized as a bank in that place;

a subsidiary of the Scheme member;
                        (Amended L.N. 107
                                of 2006)

has become bankrupt, is incapacitated by physical or mental illness, or is
                    otherwise unable or unfit to perform the functions of a member of the Board;
                    or

section.continued:
the Chief Executive may declare his office as member of the Board to be
                vacant, and shall notify the fact in such manner as the Chief Executive thinks fit;
                and upon such declaration the office becomes vacant.

subparagraph.content:
in the case of the Monetary Authority, through a person appointed
                            under section 5A(3) of the Exchange Fund Ordinance (Cap. 66) to assist the Monetary Authority;
                            and

